{"info": {"author": "Dario Meloni", "author_email": "mellon85@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "description": "# mini-api\n\nPython minimalistic HTTP(S) server\n\nSome small long running utilities don't need fancy webframeworks to offer\nsimple APIs over HTTP without any additional dependency that this module.\n\nIt spawns a thread to process incoming requests.\n\n```python\nimport mini_api\n\nserver = mini_api.Server(server_address=('localhost', 8888))\n\n@server.route('aaa')\ndef route(args):\n    return 200, 'All good'\n\nserver.start()\n\n...\n\nserver.stop()\n```\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/mellon85/mini-api", "keywords": "", "license": "BSD 3-Clause", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "mini-api", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/mini-api/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/mini-api/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/mellon85/mini-api"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/mini-api/0.1.2/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": "", "summary": "Minimalistic HTTP API with no frills", "version": "0.1.2", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>mini-api</h1>\n<p>Python minimalistic HTTP(S) server</p>\n<p>Some small long running utilities don't need fancy webframeworks to offer\nsimple APIs over HTTP without any additional dependency that this module.</p>\n<p>It spawns a thread to process incoming requests.</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">mini_api</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">server</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">mini_api</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Server</span><span class=\"p\"